name: American Record Corporation
annotation: American Record Corporation (ARC) was incorporated July 25, 1929 State of Delaware. It was owned by Consolidated Films Industries, Inc. ("CFI"). In May 1934, it acquired Columbia Phonograph Company, Inc., for $70,000, in a US Bankruptcy Court receivership auction. On Dec 17, 1938, ARC was sold by CFI to '''[http://beta.musicbrainz.org/label/27795d9f-3994-4643-9cd2-c5f2b304472d|Columbia Broadcasting Systems]'''. It was renamed "Columbia Phonograph Company, Inc." in the State of New York April 4, 1939, but then re-incorporated in Delaware May 22, 1939 as "Columbia Recording Corporation". In 1947, it was renamed  '''[http://beta.musicbrainz.org/label/7b94f338-4985-445c-b65b-1dcf41b80c16|Columbia Records, Inc.]'''). CBS remained it's parent until 1992, when all was sold to Sony.

name: Monitor-EMI
annotation: since ca. 1994, this separate (and supposedly non-existent) distribution company had been used by [http://beta.musicbrainz.org/label/1e69ab19-5f38-40e9-85ab-ac95a3f86ccc|Monitor Records spol. s r.o.] (1992–1999) and its subsidiary [http://www.discogs.com/label/289356|Monitor Slovakia, spol. s r.o.], and later [http://beta.musicbrainz.org/label/753a361b-9684-4573-a482-ff836e93e927|Monitor-EMI s.r.o.] (1999–2001), until ca. end 2001. EMI eventually bought Monitor, after which Monitor-EMI s.r.o. was renamed [http://beta.musicbrainz.org/label/5534ae37-96f2-49e7-bead-5c35ffbf9799|EMI Czech Republic s.r.o.], and the imprint [http://musicbrainz.org/label/4b82ce76-9147-4405-a07a-75d16e69dae6|Monitor] in turn became a sub-label of EMI.

name: Leguan
annotation: The label name was originally a word-play on the type of music being released on it (Goa trance) and "leguan" being German for the iguana in the logo. The "LEGO" in the "LEGOAN" logo was considered too similar to the famous toy trademark so the name was changed.Some of the early compilations still on sale at that date under the LEGOAN imprint were released with a LEGUAN sticker covering the old logo on the back.

name: Tell Me That You Love Me
Magic Records
annotation: MAGIC Records is a specialized label in the reissue of " variety " artists of the 50's, 60’s, 70’s and 80’s. This work of reissue will permit to discover or rediscover recordings only owned by the collectors, most of the time very demanded by the general public. MAGIC chooses the recordings in the repertory of the most prestigious artists of these decades.A collector packaging, but also a selection of rare or unissued titles in CD. Systematic remastering from the original masters tapes. The CD is provided with a booklet: original sleeves copies and french historical information. Each volume gathers for each artist, all the 7’’ 4 titles and 2 titles completed by rare or unissued titles.

name: E.A.R.S.
annotation:
[https://musicbrainz.org/label/856ea9ef-7f27-43e4-bec9-94d0850c1795|Electronics Arts, Inc.] (parent company):
- Created the music publishing label [https://musicbrainz.org/label/2728df23-098c-4230-96e3-09e09279b00b|E.A.R.S.] (EA™ Recordings) in 2005
- Succeeded this with the new music label [https://musicbrainz.org/label/718b1e20-f548-49f7-a377-6c4392c26d95|EA Music] in 2016. The rights holder for these credits is sometimes listed as [https://musicbrainz.org/label/7a68d19f-8ffa-4ecd-88b1-6a0beb0cd094|Electronic Arts Music].

Is reissuing most of its back catalogue online using the EA Music label - watch for the EA Music logo added onto artwork, and for these releases see if you can find the reissue date (e.g. post-2015) using a tool like https://atisket.pulsewidth.org.uk/
